    "analysis": "The metric analysis narrowed candidates to a few services among the allowed five: ts-route-service (socket spikes), ts-auth-service (cpu and diskio spikes), and ts-travel-service (several resource KPIs with breaches). ts-order-service and ts-travel-service show 'error' KPI p95=0 which is non-actionable unless >0 errors appear. Next, per the workflow we must use traces to localize among these service-level candidates — traces can show which service is downstream in call chains and whether latency/error/row_count anomalies coincide with metric faults. We'll perform trace-level threshold calculation (global P95 per trace feature across full series) and then count breaches in the incident window to see which trace series (and services) show anomalies during the incident window. This will help determine the downstream faulty service if multiple services are metric-faulty.",
