    "analysis": "The trace analysis shows no actionable non-zero error_rate anomalies during the incident window — most error_rate series have global P95=0 and values=0, which falsely count as 'breaches' when using >=P95. Metrics narrowed likely faulty candidates among the allowed components to: ts-route-service (socket spikes around 2024-01-24T22:56:00Z), ts-auth-service (cpu and diskio spikes around 2024-01-24T22:51:00Z and 23:01:00Z), and ts-travel-service (mem/socket/latency spikes ~23:00–23:08Z). Since trace error rates do not indicate failures, the next step is log analysis to determine whether any of these candidate services produced error logs or unusual log volumes during the incident window and to inspect error_logs for any textual messages tied to these services/timestamps.",
