    "instruction": "For each candidate cmdb_id in [\"ts-auth-service\",\"ts-route-service\",\"ts-travel-service\",\"ts-order-service\",\"ts-train-service\"] do the following using metric.csv: 1) For each (cmdb_id,kpi_name) compute the global P95 using the full available series. 2) Filter the metric rows to the incident window 2024-01-24 22:44:04 UTC through 2024-01-24 23:14:04 UTC. 3) For that window, produce a compact summary per (cmdb_id,kpi_name) with these fields: cmdb_id, kpi_name, p95_full, count_points_in_window, count_points_ge_p95_in_window, earliest_timestamp_ge_p95_in_window (UTC or NaT if none), max_value_in_window, longest_consecutive_run_length_of_values_ge_p95_in_window, start_timestamp_of_longest_run_in_window (UTC or NaT). Limit returned rows to only KPI groups that have count_points_ge_p95_in_window > 0, and limit output to top 50 rows sorted by longest_consecutive_run_length desc then count_points_ge_p95_in_window desc. (Use pd.to_datetime(..., unit='s', utc=True) for parsing timestamps.)"
