}

{
    "analysis": "The focused trace analysis confirms there were no non-zero trace error_rate events in the incident window — the P95==0 artifact caused zeros to appear as breaches. Metrics identified actionable anomalies for a small set of allowed services: ts-route-service (socket, small latency spikes ~22:56–23:03Z), ts-auth-service (CPU/diskio spikes ~22:51 & 23:01Z), ts-travel-service (mem/socket/workload/latency ~23:00–23:08Z), and ts-order-service (diskio spike ~23:10Z). Logs show short log.row_count spikes for some of these services but no error_count >0 and error_logs returned no textual errors. To localize the root cause we must determine which of these service-level faults is the most downstream faulty service in call chains and whether trace durations/throughput (not error_rate) show correlated anomalies at the metric breach timestamps. The next step is to inspect non-error trace features (row_count, duration_mean, duration_p95) for traces involving these candidate services within the incident window to see which service shows downstream latency/throughput anomalies that align with the metric faults.",
